area of the leak since it was discovered in the early afternoon and 
described the gaseous release as a miminum health hazard that 
created a terrible odor 
most crude oils in texas have sulphur in them and that means 
their gas containes hydrogen sulfide which is listed as one of the 
hazardous chemicals said chevron spokesman art spencer 
hydrogen sulfide is a flammable poisonous gas with a 
characteristic odor of rotten eggs 
