jail sentence 
the seven were detained after seeking to lay flowers in memory of 
jan palach the student who burned himself to death 20 years earlier 
to protest the sovietled invasion that quashed communist reforms in 
czechoslovakia 
the arrests came during a week of protests that were the largest 
in prague since palachs death 
ota veverka one of the seven charter 77 human rights group 
