grant was a banker from madison a rural town in northern 
florida when he first won election to the house in 1986 after four 
years in floridas state senate 
his conversion tips the balance of floridas delegation to 
congress giving the state 10 republicans and nine democrats 
grant is the second florida congressman to switch parties in five 
years former democratic rep andy ireland became a republican in 
1984 
grants district is the largest geographically east of the 
mississippi river the 2nd congressional district stretches along 
the states northern border from near panama city to just west of 
jacksonville and includes tallahasse the state capital 
voters in the florida panhandle have long voted for democratics 
in state elections but recently have been showing more support for 
republican candidates especially in the last two presidential 
elections 
