<TEXT>
states may not offer the equivalent of patent 
protection for utilitarian and design ideas left unprotected by 
federal law the supreme court ruled unanimously today 
the justices killed a lawsuit in which a florida boat 
manufacturer charged that its design for a fiberglass recreational 
boat was duplicated illegally by a competitor 
the court said only congress and not individual states can 
decide at some future date to protect certain industrial design 
ideas 
it is for congress to determine if the present system of design 
and utility patents is ineffectual in promoting the useful arts in 
the context of industrial design justice sandra day oconnor 
wrote for the court 
she said a florida law that would have protected the boat 
manufacturers design conflicts with the strong federal policy 
favoring free competition in ideas which do not merit patent 
protection 
bonito boats inc in 1976 developed an original hull design that 
was marketed as model 5vbr 
a hardwood model was created from engineering drawings and the 
model was then sprayed with fiberglass to create a mold the mold 
then was used to produce the finished fiberglass boats for sale 
no patent was obtained for the utilitarian or design aspects of 
the hull or for the process by which the hull was manufactured 
after the model 5vbr proved a marketing success the florida 
legislature enacted a law that in effect gave bonita boats a 
statelevel monopoly for making hulls that way 
bonito boats later invoked the state law in suing thunder craft 
boats for allegedly using the same process a florida trial judge 
upheld by the state supreme court threw out the lawsuit after 
ruling that the state law giving protection to bonito boats 
creativity impermissibly conflicts with federal patent law 
todays decision upheld the state court rulings 
congress has considered extending various forms of limited 
protection to industrial design either through the copyright laws or 
by relaxing the restrictions on the availability of design 
patents oconnor noted 
congress explicitly refused to take this step in the copyright 
laws and despite sustained criticism for a number of years it has 
declined to alter the patent protections presently available for 
industrial design she said 
the case is bonito boats vs thunder craft boats 871346 
