communist leaders have asked historians 
and jurists to determine whether political trials in the 1950s were 
rigged an official said tuesday 
the move could be a step toward rehabilitating leaders of the 
1956 anticommunist uprising some of whom were executed and buried 
in unmarked graves 
the communist party leadership on the second and final day of a 
central committee meeting also heard a report on the new 
constitution which is to leave out any reference to the leading 
role of the party and allow a multiparty system 
gyoergy fejti secretary of the party central committee said the 
party has asked that a panel of legal experts and historians look 
into the period from 1946 to 1962 to expose any possibility of 
rigged procedures at trials conducted during that period 
in search of a public consensus we must strive to see that 
suitable amends are made to those affected within the rehabilitation 
process fejti told a news conference at the close of the meeting 
but he appealed for patience and understanding saying the 
historical review would take time and we dont know what the 
results will be 
the announcement came less than 10 days after the 108member 
central committee partially reassessed the 1956 revolt that meeting 
was provoked by leading reformer imre pozsgay who said the revolt 
that for 32 years was termed a counterrevolution was a popular 
uprising 
the leadership of the ruling hungarian socialist workers 
communist party reached a compromise formulation saying the revolt 
had both popular and counterrevolutionary elements 
the revolt led by imre nagy against the regime of the stalinist 
matyas rakosi started oct 23 1956 and was brought to a bloody 
end nov 4 that year when it was quashed by soviet troops 
nagy and his associates were executed in june 1958 according to 
a ministry of justice decree issued at the time he and his 
associates were sentenced to death for conspiracy to overthrow the 
hungarian peoples democratic system 
there have been repeated calls in hungary for the rehabilitation 
of nagy and his associates authorities announced recently that they 
would allow their reburial in marked graves 
the purpose of the meeting ending tuesday was to review main 
concepts in the new constitution that will allow a multiparty 
system place greater emphasis on human and civil rights and 
strengthen political institutions including giving the president 
and parliament a larger role 
fejti presented the main concepts of the new constitution which 
is to be adopted next year 
we do not see the need and sense of the constitutional 
formulation on the leading role of the communist party he was 
quoted by the official mti news agency as saying 
however he added that this does not mean that the hswp 
hungarian socialist workers party renounces the political effort 
and intention that it wishes to remain the determining factor of the 
social processes mti said 
justice ministry officials said in december that the draft of the 
new constitution did not contain a reference to the leading role of 
the party 
fejti said it is necessary to set down in the new law the 
criteria that groups will be allowed to form if they are in 
harmony with the values and efforts formulated in the constitution 
