new opec figures he said show member nations complied in 
january with the new output accord the agreedment set an overall 
ceiling or quota of 185 million barrels a day for the 13 nations 
in the first six months of this year 
according to opec figures 12 countries supplied a total of 1742 
million barrels a day in january just under the quota of 1751 
million barrels 
the cartel said figures from the united arab emirates had not yet 
been received that nation however has persistently overshot its 
target in the past according to private analysts its current quota 
is 988000 barrels a day 
